Ad Text:
We're partnering with a purpose-driven organisation operating at scale across Australia and New Zealand, currently investing heavily in its data and platform foundations. This is a senior role within a small, growing data team, with real influence over how data, analytics, and AI are delivered across the business.

The organisation is in a growth phase, modernising its data stack and looking for someone who enjoys building reliable, well-designed data systems that people actually use.

Salary - $160k-$170k Base + Super + Bonus + Benefits
Location - Sydney or Melbourne 
Hybrid - 3 days/week | Highly Flexible 

What You’ll Do:
Build and evolve a modern cloud-based data platform that supports analytics, operational reporting, and emerging AI use cases
Own the design and implementation of data pipelines and streaming workflows, from ingestion through to consumption
Shape how data is modelled, exposed, and used across the organisation - not just how it’s moved
Work closely with analytics, product, and operational teams to turn ambiguous requirements into well-defined data assets
Contribute to platform reliability, performance, and cost optimisation as data volume and usage grow
Implement infrastructure and platform changes using code-first, automated approaches
Improve how data quality, lineage, and observability are handled across the platform
Support real-time and event-driven use cases where appropriate
Help establish standards, patterns, and best practices across data engineering and platform work
Act as a senior technical voice in a small team - influencing architecture, tooling, and ways of working
What You’ll Bring
Strong experience building data platforms or large-scale data pipelines in cloud-native environments
Hands-on expertise with AWS and modern analytical platforms such as Snowflake
Confident working with Python and SQL in production data systems
Experience transforming and modelling data using tools like dbt or similar frameworks
Familiarity with event-driven or streaming architectures (e.g. Kafka or similar technologies)
Practical experience with infrastructure as code (Terraform or equivalent)
Exposure to CI/CD practices for data or platform workloads
An engineering mindset — comfortable with version control, testing, automation, and system design trade-offs
Clear communicator who can work across engineering, analytics, and non-technical stakeholders
If you have any questions about this role or others we have available you can email us directly via data@thedrivegroup.com.au

Ad Text:
Contribute to the welfare of Australians by supporting efficient and reliable government payments and collections

Support key modernisation initiatives as Australia's payment landscape is transformed

Be part of a professional, collaborative team with strong opportunities to develop your skills


About the business/role/team

The RBA's Banking Department (BK) provides a range of banking services to Australian Government departments, agencies, overseas central banks and official institutions (customers). You'll join the Product, Risk & Analysis team, reporting to the Data & Analytics Manager. The team drives greater data literacy and empowers staff to use data more effectively, boosting efficiency, improving customer outcomes, and reinforcing robust data management across the department.


About the role

Build and enhance data pipelines that improve productivity and provide insights for internal and external stakeholders

Manage the full data lifecycle from ingestion and storage through to documentation and ongoing stewardship

Deliver analysis and insights by transforming complex datasets into clear, actionable findings




About you

Proficient in SQL and R, with experience querying data within large or complex environments.

Strong data lifecycle management capability with experience proposing and implementing strategic data initiatives.

An effective communicator, able to translate business needs into clear data requirements and turn analysis back into actionable insights.

Desirable: experience in payments, government and/or regulatory environments, or working with high‑integrity operational data.




Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

About Cbus
Created by workers, for workers, Cbus Super is one of Australia’s most successful Superannuation funds. For over four decades we’ve proudly represented those who help shape Australia, hard-working individuals who deserve to make the most of their retirement, no matter the industry. As an award-winning fund we’ve been recognised for the benefits provided to our members and our innovative investment approach.  All while staying committed to our member first ethos as a proud Industry Fund.

About the role
This role is part of the Investment Enablement team, which exists to support Cbus’ Investments front office to implement the investment strategy, mitigate operational risk and deliver reporting to support decision making.  

This newly created position offers a unique opportunity to build out and enhance the existing reporting framework and processes related to Investments, whilst influencing automation and process enhancement.  Operating with a high degree of autonomy, the role will also closely collaborate with key internal and external stakeholders. Perform analysis of investment data from the custodian, fund managers and third-party suppliers to ensure accuracy of information.

You will lead the end-to-end process for APRA reporting relating to Investments and the reporting of the Fund’s semi-annual Portfolio Holdings Disclosure for ASIC according to requirements.

The role requires strong capability and understanding of investment products, superannuation regulations, and operational processes.

prior experience in an analytical role within a superannuation fund, investment management company or custodian;
Prior experience in APRA regulatory reporting along with a demonstrated understanding of current APRA reporting obligations, including the additional obligations as part of APRA’s Superannuation Data Transformation (SDT) Phase 2 Program is ideal.

Belong at Cbus
We value difference, and embrace people with diverse backgrounds, experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. We believe that, with diversity of perspectives and experiences, you get better teams and outcomes. We’re looking for people of all genders, races, nationalities, orientations and of all abilities to join us.
  
We’re keen to hear from you
If you've read through the requirements of this role and you feel like you haven’t fully met the criteria, we would still encourage you to apply. We're aware of accessibility barriers when it comes to applying for a job and we want to help. If you require assistance with your application, please contact our Talent Acquisition Team via careers@cbussuper.com.au 

Like to know more about working with Cbus? Listen to some of our videos with members of the Cbus team on our website, cbussuper.com.au/careers
  
Applications Close: 11 February
This is a full time role based in Melbourne.
  
Agencies, please note: All Cbus vacancies are managed by our internal Talent Acquisition Team.  Should external assistance be required we will reach out to our preferred agency partners, Thank you.

Baseline Clearance Required 
12 Month Contract + 2 X 12 Month Extension 
3 days WFH from Canberra or Melbourne

The Senior Business Analyst will be required to:

Ad Text:
About the Role

Sime Industrial is expanding its Corporate Finance team. In this role, you will play a pivotal role in evaluating new opportunities, supporting transactions, and shaping the company's long term growth strategy both in Australia as well as internationally.

This is a role that will be perfect for someone with foundational financial modelling and presentation exposure and you should be a naturally curious, adaptable, and hands‑on person.

You will be supported by senior team members (all with Big4 Corporate Finance / M&A background) and have the opportunity to broaden your experience across multiple markets and countries.

Further, you will:

Provide sound commercial analysis and recommendations to identify and develop growth and cost reduction strategies
Evaluate and communicate financial and operational performance trends, historical and forecast, to support decision making
Support the full deal cycle for acquisitions, joint ventures, divestitures, and new project developments
Build and maintain financial models with guidance from experienced team members
Prepare investment papers, presentations, and insights for senior leadership
Assist in coordinating due diligence across internal teams and external advisors
Provide budgeting, forecasting and business planning activities support, and assist monthly, quarterly and annual business performance reviews
Perform internal and external performance benchmarking
Influence a continuous improvement of culture and change management
Provide the Senior Leadership Team with commentary, analysis and proactive improvements to enable the business to make more informed decisions and prompt profitability


Who We Are

Sime is a partner of choice for some of the world's best brands in the Industrial and Motors sectors. With operations in 17 countries and territories and a strong footprint in Asia Pacific, we continue to grow, delivering sustainable value to our stakeholders through operational excellence, high-performance standards and good corporate governance.

Why Sime?

You'll have access to:

Opportunities for training, mentorship, and career development specific to your role.
Competitive remuneration package and annual salary reviews.
Access to growth opportunities at a regional, national, and international level through our global Sime network.
Dedicated programs and utilities to support your physical, mental, and financial health, such as our Employee Assistance Program, free health checks, and discounted private health insurance.
Employee discounts, rewards, and incentive programs.
Paid parental leave options.
Salary continuance insurance.


About You

A successful teammate will have experience in:

At least 4 years of relevant experience in a similar role (professional services experience will be advantageous)
Commercially focused finance professional with strong analytical and modelling skills
Experienced in evaluating and communicating financial and operational performance to support decision‑making
Exposure to the full deal lifecycle, including investments, acquisitions and due diligence
Confident in preparing investment papers and executive‑level presentations
Collaborative, proactive and driven to continuously improve performance and profitability

Job Title: Program Risk Management and Analytics Lead
Company: Games Independent Infrastructure and Coordination Authority
Ad Text:
About the Role

The Program Risk Management and Analytics Lead, provides expert analytical oversight and strategic insight across GIICA’s Corporate, Program, and Project risk management frameworks. The position ensures the integrity, accuracy, and reliability of risk data by identifying patterns, trends, and anomalies that inform proactive decision-making and strengthen organisational assurance. The role drives an integrated, whole-of-Games approach to risk management by analysing information across the Games Coordination, Olympic and Paralympic Games Office, and ensuring compliance with the Risk Management and Assurance Policy for the Games Enterprise Group (GEG) and Games Leadership Group (GLG). The role develops high-level risk reports that enhance the collective understanding of Executive Steering Committees, the Executive Leadership Team and the Board, enabling timely, evidence-based decisions on complex and emerging risks. The position supports the General Manager Risk and Assurance in overseeing GIICA’s risk management frameworks and facilitating effective stakeholder and interagency coordination. Through ongoing monitoring of project and program risk data, the role ensures alignment with GIICA’s Risk Appetite and contributes to a mature, transparent, and integrated approach to risk management across the organisation.

The role is fast paced and operates in a complex, high-profile and often changing environment.

In joining the Authority, you will join a team of hard-working professionals, dedicated to preparing Queensland for the 2032 Olympic and Paralympic Games.

About the Authority

The Games Independent Infrastructure and Coordination Authority (GIICA) is laying the foundations for the 2032 Olympic and Paralympic Games and beyond.  

Hosting the world’s largest sporting celebration is a privilege that will define Queensland for the rest of the 21st century, driving economic growth, sustainability, connectivity, and healthier, more-inclusive communities.  

GIICA will deliver 17 new and upgraded venues, from Brisbane’s Main Stadium to key sporting infrastructure across the state.  We are building a legacy that transcends the Games, transforming Queensland to ensure we thrive on the world stage showcasing our vision, culture and lifestyle.   

GIICA is committed to delivering exceptional service and accelerating our state's transformation by bringing together communities, industries and governments.  We are ensuring every project we deliver for the world's largest sporting celebration is making a transformational difference to the Queensland community.

About your Responsibilities

Analyse the data integrity of the risk management information as part of Corporate, Program and Project frameworks including identifying and reporting patterns, trends and anomalies.

Analyse information as part of the integrated Games Co-ordination, Olympic and Paralympic Games Office approach to the risk management process including compliance with the Risk Management and Assurance Policy by GEG and GLG.

Analyse and develop high level risk management reports which will assist in the collective understanding of the respective Executive Steering Committees, the Executive Leadership Team and the Board to enable effective decision making.

Assist the General Manager Risk and Assurance in the oversight and management of the GIICA Risk Management Frameworks and ensuring effective Stakeholder and Interagency Co-ordination.

Monitor the Project and Program risk management data for compliance and alignment with the GIICA Risk Appetite.

About You

Tertiary qualifications in risk management, business, engineering, analytics, project management, or a related discipline, or equivalent demonstrated experience in complex program or multi-agency environments.

Extensive experience analysing risk data within corporate, program and project risk frameworks, including the ability to identify patterns, trends, anomalies, and emerging risk indicators.

Demonstrated capability in developing high-level risk reports and insights for executive governance bodies such as Steering Committees, Executive Leadership Teams and Boards.

Strong understanding of enterprise risk management principles, assurance frameworks, and the application of organisational Risk Appetite to complex projects and programs.

Proven experience applying risk management processes within integrated or multi-agency environments, ideally involving government, delivery partners, or major event coordination bodies.

High-level analytical skills, including proficiency with risk systems, data analysis tools, and the ability to translate complex information into clear, actionable insights.

Well-developed communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to work effectively across agencies, facilitate coordination, and provide authoritative advice to senior stakeholders.

Demonstrated ability to support risk framework oversight, governance processes, and compliance monitoring within large, multi-layered programs.

About our Workplace

At GIICA, we’re building a workplace that reflects the legacy we’re delivering: Inclusive, agile, and purpose driven. We value diversity, respect, and equity, fostering a culture where everyone feels safe, supported, and empowered to contribute. Our fast-paced environment calls for sharp judgement, adaptability, and a solution-focused mindset. As a newly formed authority, we embrace change and innovation, offering a rare opportunity to shape best-practice processes from the ground up. This is a once-in-a-lifetime chance to grow your career while helping transform Queensland’s future.

How to apply

Please submit:

Your current CV

1 page cover letter outlining your relevant experience in similar roles, and how you believe you are the right person for this position.

Applications close at 5pm Wednesday 11 February 2026 AEST. We encourage candidates to apply early, as we will be reviewing applications as they are received.

For any queries regarding this role, please contact careers@giica.au (however all applications must be received via seek.com.au).  

Join the Authority and take this once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to help create a more inclusive, sustainable and connected society – all because we are hosting the Games.

Additional information 

Applications from candidates with full working rights for the full duration of the appointment will only be accepted.  Visa sponsorship is not available for this role.

A probationary period of six months will apply.

Applications remain current for 12 months and may be considered for identical or similar vacancies.

Successful applicants will be required to undergo pre-employment checks as part of our recruitment and selection process, which may include the following: 

Criminal history check

Evidence of your right to work in Australia

Disclosure of any previous serious disciplinary action taken against you.

Disclosure of any employment as a lobbyist (must be provided within one month of taking up the appointment)

Your personal information will be held securely and accessed only by those directly involved in the recruitment process. Information obtained through employment screening is treated confidentially and will only be used to assess your suitability for employment with us and your contribution to our diverse workforce.

Will you actively create a healthier future for tomorrow?



At Medibank we're encouraged to think big. We have a clear purpose to impact better health outcomes for our customers, patients and our community.



We celebrate diversity of thought because we want to make better decisions for our customers. As we work towards our goal of better health for better lives, we value the knowledge and contribution of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders. We are working hard to create an inclusive workplace and develop Indigenous careers.



Medibank has bold 2030 Vision to deliver the best health and wellbeing for Australia increasingly relies on succeeding in Digital. Digital platforms and engineering services will be a critical enabler for future health and insurance experiences we deliver to our customers. The current Digital platforms have strong capabilities but for us to win in the context of 2030 vision, our digital assets will need to be reimagined and further evolved that is scalable, increases agility and accelerate solution delivery with improved security posture. 



About the Role



We're looking for a Junior-Mid Data Solution Designer or experienced Data Analyst to join the team on a 6‑month contract, earning $650 per day. You'll be working alongside two senior designers who will support your development as you grow your data modelling and solution design skills.



This opportunity is perfect for someone with around 3-5 years' experience who is confident with SQL, comfortable investigating and interpreting data, and ready to expand their capability in data design. You'll manage your own work while learning from senior team members and contributing to meaningful enhancements across the data environment.

Key Responsibilities



Work closely with senior designers to understand existing data solutions and contribute to enhancements.
Use SQL to query, investigate, and interpret data accurately and efficiently.
Support the development of end‑to‑end data flows, including how data is sourced, stored, and transformed.
Contribute to data model development using Kimball and Data Lake concepts.
Translate business requirements into clear technical documentation and simple solution outlines.
Conduct data profiling and basic source-to-target mapping.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to clarify requirements and communicate findings.
Work within cloud environments (AWS preferred; general cloud experience is fine).

What We're Looking For



Around 3 - 5 years' experience in data analysis, data design, or a similar data‑focused role.
Strong SQL skills and confidence working with large datasets.
Comfortable querying, interpreting, and validating data.
Exposure to data modelling concepts and a willingness to build deeper design expertise.
Experience with AWS or other cloud platforms (general knowledge is sufficient).
Strong communication skills and ability to work with both business and technical stakeholders.
Independent, proactive, and able to manage your own workload effectively.
Curious mindset, strong analytical thinking, and eagerness to learn from senior team members.



What Success Looks Like



You'll be able to:



Quickly understand the existing data environment and how key hubs operate.
Independently handle your own analysis and SQL work.
Contribute to design discussions with guidance from senior designers.
Provide clear documentation and logical data insights.
Grow your data modelling and solution design capability over the course of the engagement.



A career with us

At Medibank, we believe work is something we do, not somewhere we go. Our modes of working - Collaboration, Connection and Concentration - help inform how your day is structured and where you choose to work will vary, depending on your role and requirements.  


The wellbeing of our employees is our priority. We encourage you to talk to us about any additional support you may require during the recruitment process, as well as how this role can be flexible for you. We encourage applications from candidates with a disability, if you require any adjustments or alternate formats of key information at any stage of the recruitment process, we welcome hearing from you.

Responsibilities




Leadership & Strategy

Define and own the marketing intelligence roadmap.
Build and lead a high-performing team of analysts, engineers, and data scientists.
Partner with Growth, Data, Finance and Product Marketing leadership to enable data-driven decisions.

Measurement & Modelling

Lead the design and deployment of multi-touch attribution (MTA) and probabilistic attribution approaches.
Champion marketing mix modelling (MMM) to measure cross-channel ROI and incrementality.
Advance predictive analytics for LTV, churn, and customer journey optimisation, leveraging AI-powered models for greater accuracy.

AI, GenAI & Automation

Deploy AI and machine learning models for anomaly detection, predictive spend optimization, and customer segmentation.

Introduce Generative AI (GenAI) solutions for:

Automated campaign insights (“explain spend efficiency by channel in natural language”).
Dynamic customer journey clustering to identify emerging cohorts.
Generating personalized marketing narratives and creative testing at scale.
Build a culture of automation where insights flow seamlessly into marketing strategy and execution.

Data Infrastructure & Governance

Oversee marketing data pipelines and modelling powered by AppsFlyer, Databricks, Google Marketing Platform, and Google BigQuery.
Ensure strong data governance, quality, and compliance with GDPR, CCPA, ATT, and other privacy regulations.

Reporting & Insights

Develop and maintain high-impact dashboards in Tableau.
Deliver regular insights that guide marketing investment and strategy, supported by automated reporting and GenAI-driven summaries for executives.
Act as the bridge between advanced AI/ML outputs and marketing strategy, ensuring models directly influence spend and creativity.

Are you looking for an awesome place to work, where you can proudly be your authentic self, and be part of #oneteam?

We are looking for a passionate team player who aligns with our values and culture, takes pride in their unique contributions, and can challenge the status quo with disruptive thinking. If this sounds like you, come and join us!

Reporting to the Head of Pricing and Commercial Deals, the role provides pricing management and deal evaluation across Enterprise, Wholesale, and Government customer segments. This role is an important position in the organisation responsible for yield management and customer deal outcomes.

What you’ll be doing day-to-day  

Execute pricing strategy
Price modelling and analysis focussed on winning new business and retention, working closely with Sales and Products teams
Evaluate and provide recommendations on customer pricing proposals
Support bids that require non-standard pricing
Review and approve pricing skeletals/price books
Manage yield and deal outcomes.

What you’ll bring to this role  

2+ years’ experience in evaluating pricing or commercial proposals in a B2B environment
Telco or ICT experience ideal but not essential
High performing individual with excellent financial modelling and analytical skills
High level of detail orientation and sound commercial acumen  
Strong interpersonal engagement skills and service orientation be naturally “hands on” with an ability to work efficiently and effectively as part of a small team
Ability to communicate and present complex financial information to a wide audience.

What We Offer 

Working at Vocus will give you rewarding experiences and the opportunity to do extraordinary work. You will enjoy: 

Diverse and dynamic teams with a supportive and inclusive culture. 
Supportive career development plans with comprehensive ongoing training, support, and development opportunities. 
Generous discounts to over 400 retailers. 
Competitive leave options, including anniversary leave, purchased leave, parental leave, volunteering leave, study leave, and 5 extra days of Vocus leave each year, plus more.
Study assistance programs to excel your personal growth, learning and development. 
Health and wellness offerings, including access to our wellbeing initiatives that can help you from a financial, psychological, and physical perspective. 

Working at Vocus is never just a job – it’s personal. We’re crazy about our customers and believe our people are the difference. Our wonderfully diverse team and a vibrant culture define us. We care about the impact we have on our people, our customers, and our communities and are committed to operating as a responsible, ethical business. 

We pride ourselves on setting audacious and ambitious goals and believe that we can play our part in changing the Australian telecommunications landscape and make a fundamental difference to people’s lives. 

With us, you’ll have the opportunity to lead and inspire teams, work on projects that are shaping the future of telecommunications and become part of a culture that thrives on creativity, encourages new ideas, and provides a collaborative and inclusive environment.  

About Us 

As Australia’s specialist fibre and network solutions provider, we own and operate 25,000km of secure, high-capacity fibre connecting people, businesses, governments, and communities across Australia to the world. Through our well-known retail brands, we deliver simple and affordable broadband, mobile, voice and energy services with the purpose of Building Critical Connections. Enabling Better Possibilities.  

Ready to take the next step? 

If you like the sound of this role and think you’d do a great job, but are worried you don’t tick every box, we encourage you to back yourself – we know that diverse groups are less-likely to apply for roles they’re not 100% qualified for, but just as likely to succeed at them!  

We are a proud equal opportunity employer committed to providing a safe, diverse, and inclusive working environment where all our team members feel like they belong. We know diversity makes us stronger and we encourage applications irrespective of background, age, origin, gender, sexual orientation, identity, or ability.   

If you feel comfortable, please let us know if you have any accessibility requirements upon application, so we can make any adjustments required to support you throughout our recruitment process.

The Role

As a Senior Energy Market Analyst, you will play a pivotal role in supporting our Wholesale team across trading, origination, and investment functions. This position focuses on market modelling, risk management, and revenue forecasting for both traditional energy retail and renewable sectors, including solar, wind, and Battery Energy Storage Systems (BESS). You will also lead project management for renewable assets and deliver actionable insights to senior management.

Key Responsibilities

· Wholesale Energy Risk Management: Develop models to assist in risk management and cost analysis across wholesale inputs (Electricity, Gas, Renewables), AEMO prudential requirements, environmental certificates, retail cost stacks, and pricing/tariffs.

· Energy Trading Strategy Development: Support trading strategies and provide contract trading capability via OTC and broker markets, PPAs, ASX futures, and environmental certificate markets.

· Market Modelling & Reporting: Build and maintain models to assess requirements for wholesale electricity purchase agreements, VPP agreements, battery storage supply agreements, and new product offerings in residential markets.

· Renewable Asset Development: Provide input and project management support for potential renewable assets, ensuring timely evaluation and integration into the portfolio.

Academic & Professional Qualifications
Essential:

· Degree or postgraduate qualification in Engineering, Economics, Mathematics, Finance, Actuarial Studies, or similar.

· Proven track record in providing market insights that support commercial decisions.

· Minimum of 1-2 years of experience in energy markets analysis, modelling, or trading analytics.

· Strong communicator with ability to translate complex market analysis into actionable insights.

· Australian work rights are required for this position.

Desirable:

· 3–6 years of relevant professional experience in energy markets analysis, modelling, or trading analytics.

· Hands-on experience with market modelling tools.

· Strong understanding of wholesale electricity markets, ancillary service markets, and renewable/storage project economics.

· Previous experience in energy trading, risk management, or financial markets.

· Previous experience in project management of renewable energy assets.

Personal Qualities

· Achievement orientated, humanistic, and affiliative.

· Steady, calm, reliable, trustworthy, enthusiastic, and resilient.

Technical Skills

· Proficiency in Python, R, SQL, Excel, and energy market simulation software.

· Intermediate proficiency in Python is required for this role.

· Basic query proficiency in SQL is required for this role.

· Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills.

· Strong organisational and project management capabilities.

Why Join Us?

· Be part of a dynamic team shaping the future of energy in Australia.

· Work on innovative renewable projects and cutting-edge market strategies.

· Enjoy a collaborative environment with strong career growth pathways.

Ready to make an impact? Apply now and help us deliver smarter energy solutions for a sustainable future.

Job Title: Product and Infrastructure Performance Insights Lead
Ad Text:
Product & Infrastructure Performance Insights Lead

You will be responsible for leading the development and implementation of product, and infrastructure (asset and system) performance insights function that incorporates the asset performance, asset health, resilience, system health and system performance in line with product and service performance.

What you will be doing 

Asset, System and Product performance insights: develop and produce meaningful performance insights for each asset class, infrastructure system and product, outlining current and forecast performance against agreed targets and benchmarks.
Provide insight into operational licence, environmental protection licence and service performance, with a data-based view to alternative options to inform regulatory discussions considering risk / cost / performance and corporate objectives.
Inform the business managers and leads with performance, risk and cost issues by integrating multiple information systems. 
Provide insights on a monthly basis regarding performance, compliance with agreed levels of customer service and progression towards agreed goals, including reporting details of any exceptions. 

About you 

Bachelor’s qualifications in engineering, software, data science or a related discipline, or experience deemed equivalent, with demonstrated experience and skills in development and implementation of performance framework.
Demonstrated significant experience in business performance insights (e.g. service, system, asset and work delivery performance), couple with risk management, financial and economic analysis and using/developing related tools in decision making.
Demonstrated Experience in developing insights for relevant products/asset classes and integrated water cycle management.
Strong people management and leadership experience. Demonstration in forming and leading high performing teams in a positive and constructive environment to achieve management goals and objectives.
Demonstrated experience in building BI management tools for asset management decision making
Values- driven approach: A genuine commitment to Sydney Water’s signature behaviours and values.

Please see the position description for the role’s full accountabilities. For any additional questions please reach out to connor.may@sydneywater.com.au – Wednesday 11th Feb

We’re passionate about building a diverse and inclusive team, and love hearing from people like you. 

Why join us?

Lead SAP FI/CO Functional Analyst

Contract

Canberra

Excellent Federal Government Client

A SAP FI/CO (Financial Accounting / Controlling) Functional Consultant will play a critical role in managing Austrade’s financial processes and internal controlling. Austrade is looking for an SAP FI/CO Functional Consultant to join the Corporate Services Division.   

The FI/CO Functional Consultant will work closely with Corporate Systems and Finance Teams to deliver client-centred solutions. They will collaborate with the Chief Finance Officer, COO and GM Digital and Technology, and provide technical capability to create a more efficient and resilient instance of our SAP system (ECC6 on prem). 

Key duties and responsibilities

The SAP FI/CO Functional Consultant will be responsible for:  

Reviewing the existing core financial management functionality assessment and process to identify limitations and areas of improvement.  

Assessing current SAP system’s integration capabilities and customisations.  

Determine the modular functions within SAP that is currently utilised and recommend improvements that could be beneficial.  

Gathering input from finance team members and other stakeholders to understand their current problems, future needs and expectations to have a fit for purpose finance solution.   

Implementation and support of SAP Financials (focus on FICO Controlling – Cost Centre Accounting, Unsettled Costs, Month End Close, Overhead assessment, and settlement.)   

Design, customise, configure, and test various functions within FI/CO modules.  

Support End of Month and Year end closing processes and resolve issues.  

Setting up financial accounting and controlling processes.  

Engage with business stakeholders to understand their financial and controlling requirements, including identification of gaps, issues, and work around solutions.   

Identify opportunities for process improvement and optimisation of existing financial processes using SAP functionality, implementing best practice to enhance efficiency and effectiveness.  

Provide compliance and audit support to ensure that financial processes and configurations comply with relevant regulatory and accounting standards.   

Generate financial reports and financial data analytics to support business decision making.  

Maintain comprehensive documentation of configurations, customisations, and business processes.  

Triage and resolve SAP support queries in a timely manner i.e. provide support to end users, assisting with problem determination and resolution, and where possible, offering training.  

Act as a liaison between the finance functions and the technical team.   

Support capability uplift of the existing team, through mentoring and knowledge sharing to develop an effective systems governance function.  

Work self-directed and independently; may act as subject matter mentor to other business areas undertaking finance operations and activities.

Assist Internal Audit Leadership Team by leading and/or supporting the delivery the annual audit plan and non-audit related activities through use of data analytics and automation.
Perform data extraction, cleansing, and analysis across multiple sources to support audit objectives. 
Collaborate with audit teams and stakeholders to embed analytics into the audit lifecycle.
Stay current with emerging trends in Data Analytics and technology risk bringing forward practical application for audit.
Ensure quality outcomes are achieved in a timely manner, escalating all potential delays accordingly. ​
Support the delivery of audit reports that provide clarity on issues, root causes and associated risks with clearly articulated insights on the effectiveness of business processes, risk and control frameworks and / or strategy. ​
Engage and foster relationships with key stakeholders, including leadership to achieve effective outcomes, e.g. ensure deliverables are clearly articulated and potential issues are promptly identified and effectively addressed. ​
Review (as required) internal audit remediation actions committed by management. Undertake verification procedures to provide assurance that actions have been completed effectively. ​
Ensure deliverables and work products are factually accurate and convey insights which enhance the effectiveness and reputation of the internal audit function. ​
Contribute to the development of the annual risk-based Internal Audit Plan to ensure that assurance coverage remains relevant and sufficient relative to the risk profile of the organisation. ​
Maintain high standards of integrity and accountability. Facilitate the integration of risk management into day-to-day business activities and processes.​
Challenge the status quo to continuously improve processes both within the Internal Audit Unit and the areas being audited. ​
Maintain professional development, as required under the Global Internal Audit Standards (GIAS). 

Skills & Experience

Minimum 5 years experience in Audit Data Analytics including Data cleaning and preparation, Data visualisation tools, programming and reporting.
Well-developed understanding of audit procedures and standards.
Minimum 5 years experience in internal audit, and at least 3 years relevant experience in the financial services industry within the general insurance industry.
Demonstrated expertise in authoring conscious audit reports, which clearly articulate audit findings, their potential impact on business processes and associated risk and control environments.
Demonstrated experience in the adoption of technology or other operational level changes that have resulted in improving Internal Audit’s efficiency and ability to provide enhanced coverage.

Job Title: Senior Business Analyst - Data and Digital Solutions
Ad Text:
Who we are

TasPorts is a state-owned company responsible for ten Tasmanian ports and the Devonport Airport. We are a vertically integrated organisation providing a diverse range of port and marine operations and services around Tasmania. Our vision is to proudly connect people, products and solutions for the benefit of all Tasmanians.

With 99% of the State’s freight moving through our multi-port system, TasPorts facilitates vital trade to enable industry partners and communities while ensuring the highest environmental and safety standards.

The role

As we continue to modernise our operations and uplift our digital and data maturity, we’re seeking a Senior Business Analyst to play a key role in shaping the future of digital and data solutions across TasPorts.

Reporting into the IT Program Manager, the Senior Business Analyst will lead the analysis, discovery, and requirements definition that underpin our digital transformation initiatives. You’ll partner with operational, corporate, and technical stakeholders to translate business needs into actionable solution designs that support TasPorts’ strategic priorities and operational excellence.

This is a senior role ideal for someone who thrives in complex environments, enjoys engaging diverse stakeholder groups, and brings both analytical depth and strong communication capability.

Responsibilities 

Lead end-to-end business analysis across digital, data, and technology projects

Facilitate workshops, process mapping, and requirements gathering with stakeholders across ports, marine operations, corporate services, and asset management

Develop detailed business, functional, and technical requirements

Partner with project managers, solution architects, data specialists, and vendors to ensure solution alignment

Assess current-state processes and identify opportunities for optimisation, automation, and digital enhancement

Support business case development, feasibility assessments, and options analysis

Contribute to enterprise digital and data standards, ensuring solutions align with organisational strategy

Champion user experience, change readiness, and adoption throughout project delivery

This role is based in the TasPorts Hobart Corporate office.




About you

The key experience we are looking for includes: 

5+ years of demonstrated experience as a Business Analyst working on digital projects, products, or transformation initiatives.

Experience eliciting, documenting, and managing requirements throughout the project lifecycle.

Experience collaborating with multidisciplinary delivery teams.

Background supporting testing, defect triage, and validation of digital solutions against defined requirements.

Experience contributing to change readiness, user training, and adoption activities for digital solutions.

Excellent analytical and problem‑solving skills, with the ability to translate complex issues into clear, actionable insights.

What you will have

Essential

·          Relevant tertiary qualification (e.g. Bachelor of Business, IT, Data).

·          Formal training or certification in Business Analysis (e.g., IIBA ECBA, CCBA, CBAP, BPMN).

·          Current unrestricted Tasmanian drivers licence.

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Job Title: Mid-Level AI Analyst - Governance & Ethics
Location: Sydney CBD
Employment Type: Full-time / long term contract opportunity
Salary: Negotiable contract rate on offer

About the Role

We are seeking a hands-on Mid-Level AI Analyst, and this role is ideal for someone passionate about AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks, who enjoys translating complex technical risks into practical advice and solutions.
You will work across government, enterprise, and technical teams to assess AI initiatives, monitor compliance, and support the implementation of robust governance processes. This is not a policy-making role , it's analytical, advisory, and deeply hands-on, offering exposure to cutting-edge AI projects in a high-impact environment.

Key Responsibilities

Conduct AI governance and ethics assessments across projects, identifying potential risks, bias, fairness, and compliance issues.
Support implementation of AI governance frameworks, approval gates, and monitoring processes.
Collaborate with policy, IT, legal, privacy, and business teams to provide clear, actionable guidance on AI projects.
Document and report findings, including risk assessments, dashboards, and governance committee materials.
Stay up to date with AI regulatory requirements, privacy laws, and ethical AI principles, ensuring projects align with best practice.
Assist in embedding responsible AI practices and frameworks.


Skills & Experience
Essential:

Hands-on experience in AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks.
Understanding of ethical AI principles: bias/fairness, & transparency.
Experience assessing AI projects for compliance, risk, and governance concerns.
Strong analytical skills and ability to review data sets, model outputs, or AI tools.
Experience with ServiceNow or similar governance/tracking tools.
Excellent communication skills to translate technical risks into clear advice for senior management.


Desirable / Nice-to-Have:

Background in government/public sector, consulting, finance, regulated industries, academia, or tech companies with AI governance exposure.
Knowledge of AI regulatory requirements, PIAs, or model risk frameworks.
Experience supporting governance committees, dashboards, and reporting frameworks.

"If AI governance and ethics excite you, we want to hear from you!"

Job Title: Multiple roles: Business Analyst, OCM and Data Manager
Ad Text:
Federal Government ServiceNow CRM Platform – Multiple Roles

Protected Environment | Large-Scale Transformation

We are supporting the delivery of a federal government ServiceNow CRM platform, designed to enable secure, scalable, and integrated stakeholder engagement across a complex, highly regulated organisation. The platform will be delivered in phases, commencing with a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) within a protected ServiceNow environment, and evolving into an enduring, dual-platform CRM spanning internal and public-facing domains.

We are seeking experienced professionals to support delivery across data, change, training, and business analysis, working closely with senior stakeholders in a federal government environment.

Please note these roles are onsite in Canberra. Interstate applications will be ignored.




📊 Data Manager

Role Overview

The Data Manager will oversee data migration, consolidation, and governance, ensuring data is accurate, secure, and compliant across multiple enterprise systems.

Key Responsibilities

Lead CRM data migration and consolidation activities

Establish and enforce data governance and quality standards

Manage de-duplication, harmonisation, and validation processes

Support secure and compliant data outcomes in a protected environment

Key Deliverables

Data Migration Plan and Data Mapping documentation

Data Quality Assessment and Data Governance Framework

De-duplication and harmonisation reports

Data validation and post-migration verification artefacts


🔄 OCM Manager / Training Lead

Role Overview

This role is responsible for Organisational Change Management (OCM) and training delivery, ensuring stakeholders and end users are prepared, engaged, and confident in adopting new CRM processes and capabilities.

Key Responsibilities

Develop and execute OCM and training strategies

Lead stakeholder engagement and communication planning

Conduct change impact and readiness assessments

Design and deliver training materials and sessions

Support adoption, transition, and post-go-live uptake

Key Deliverables

OCM strategy, roadmap, and benchmark reporting

External stakeholder engagement and outreach strategy

Customer experience framework and feedback mechanisms

Training needs analysis and training roadmap

Quick reference guides, onboarding materials, CBT modules, videos and webinars

Training completion and adoption metrics


📋 Business Analyst

Role Overview

The Business Analyst will bridge business needs and technical delivery, ensuring CRM solutions align with organisational objectives, governance requirements, and operational priorities.

Key Responsibilities

Elicit, analyse, and document business requirements

Facilitate stakeholder workshops and engagement sessions

Develop functional and non-functional specifications

Refine and prioritise user stories

Maintain end-to-end requirements traceability

Support solution design, development, and testing

Identify and proactively manage risks, issues, and gaps

Key Deliverables

Validated business requirements and specifications

Prioritised user stories and backlog artefacts

Requirements traceability documentation

Stakeholder workshop outcomes and decision records


Why Join This Program?

Contribute to a major federal government digital transformation

Work within a Protected ServiceNow environment

Engage senior stakeholders across a large, complex organisation

Help deliver an enduring national-scale CRM capability
